DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Reticulocyte Result  Integer::1 Decimal Place Billion per Liter Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The 1 decimal place billion per liter numeric laboratory value measured, assigned or computed related to the assessment of reticulocytes in a specimen.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information relating to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for reticulocytes, immature erythrocytes that have just undergone extrusion of their cell nucleus.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: Immature erythrocytes that have just undergone extrusion of their cell nucleus. They still contain some organelles that gradually decrease in number as the cells mature.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: Immature erythrocytes that have just undergone extrusion of their cell nucleus. They still contain some organelles that gradually decrease in number as the cells mature.
